		(title "Kia Arm Controller — Root Sheet")
		(date "2026-05-27")
		(rev "v1.0-draft")
		(company "Sacha Gibert")
		(comment 1 "ESP32-S3 controller for 4-axis + gripper robotic arm")
		(comment 2 "Hierarchical: Power / MCU / IO / Connectors")
	)
	(lib_symbols)
	(text "Kia Arm Controller v1.0 — Hierarchical Root\n\nSheets:\n  • Power.kicad_sch       — Input, protections, buck VSERVO 6V/10A, buck +3V3, LDO +5V_LOGIC, INA219\n  • MCU.kicad_sch         — ESP32-S3-WROOM-1-N16R8, USB-C, debug, BOOT/RESET, LEDs\n  • IO.kicad_sch          — Pots, buttons, switch mode, buzzer, 74AHCT244 buffer\n  • Connectors.kicad_sch  — 5x servo headers, expansion, SWD\n\nGlobal nets passed between sheets:\n  Power: VIN_RAW, +VSERVO, +5V_LOGIC, +3V3, GND, GND_PWR, GND_AGND\n  Signals: PWM_*, POT_*, I2C_*, SPI_*, USB_DM, USB_DP, ~ESTOP, MODE_SEL,\n           SERVO_EN, LED_STATUS, LED_FAULT, WS2812_DI, BUZZER, ~BOOT, ~RESET,\n           UART_TX, UART_RX, EXP_IO1, EXP_IO2\n\nNotes:\n  - PCB target: 100 x 70 mm, 4 layers (SIG/GND/PWR/SIG), 2oz internal copper.\n  - Strapping pins to respect: GPIO0, 3, 45, 46.\n  - GPIO 26-37 reserved by octal PSRAM/Flash on N16R8 — DO NOT USE.\n  - See docs/03-schematic-spec.md for component-level details.\n"
